---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Support"
  description="Get support for Go Bananas. Contact info for testers, bug reports, feature requests, and feedback."
  path="/support"
>
  <section class="container-quiet page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Go Bananas</a></p>
    <h1 class="page-title">Support</h1>
    <p class="page-meta">Bug reports, feature requests, and beta access.</p>
  </section>

  <hr class="section-rule" />

  <article class="container-quiet section prose">
    <h2>How to reach us</h2>
    <p>
      Email{' '}
      <a href="mailto:feedback@bananascanner.com">feedback@bananascanner.com</a>{' '}
      for bug reports, feature requests, or anything else. Replies usually
      come within a few days.
    </p>
    <p>
      If it misreads a banana's ripeness, screenshot the result screen first.
      The diagnostic block at the bottom shows the hue values the classifier
      saw, which is the data we recalibrate from. Send that along with the
      stage you'd have called it.
    </p>

    <h2>Beta access</h2>
    <p>
      Go Bananas is in beta on iOS (TestFlight) and Android (Google Play
      internal testing). To get in,{' '}
      <a href="mailto:beta@bananascanner.com?subject=Go%20Bananas%20beta">join the beta</a>{' '}
      and mention which platform.
    </p>

    <h2>Permissions and data</h2>
    <p>
      Everything runs on your device. Nothing leaves your phone. See the{' '}
      <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full breakdown.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-head {
    padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
  }

  .page-meta {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section {
    padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
  }
</style>
